comment: is awesome. Lecture isn't necessary and she even says that from the beginning. All you need to do is read the textbook and show up for quizzes and you're golden.
I'm in his class at the moment. I have tried so hard to pay attention, but I am confident that it is impossible. Painfully boring.
Excellent teacher. Enjoys and knows his subject matter. Friendly and helpful.

His lectures were boring, but he gave us handouts to follow along with, so that was helpful. He has 2 paper (easy), 4 quizzes (easy) and two test (moderately easy. I think I would take his class again.
Didn't teach us anything. Boring.

TERRIBLE!!!! DONT TAKE with him!! He is a nice person, but his lectures were unbearably boring. The information is incredibly hard to understand from him. All he uses are graphs. It is just graph after graph after graph. Seriously consider a different class or teacher!!

Dr. J. is a nice enough guy, who certainly knows his stuff but not all people were meant to be teachers. Several times he disgustedly woke people up who were sleeping in class. Sure that's disrespectful of the student, but his monotonous droning and old fashioned overheads are somewhat responsible.
If you want to take a good nap, take his class.

Dry sense of humor. Attendence is a MUST!! He gives 4 pop-quizzes. Lectures weren't very exciting, he uses overheads straight from the textbook. Dr.  is very informative. Mid-term and final were difficult but do-able. It is best to read the textbook before class

Dr.  online class is a mess. Dates and assignments are frequently wrong/ unpublished. She also does not post what is due for the week's module until Monday, which means that you can never plan ahead for this class (due dates are on the Sunday of that week). Takes forever to grade and provides very little feedback.
Her class was very easy, the last 2 exams were open note
Do you Sona studies early, that is the best advice I can give to any student taking intro psych. Dr.  was a great professor, be sure to study, and start studying early!!

Mr.  is very knowledgeable and enthusiastic about political parties. He is a great teacher, but sometimes his lectures can be a bit dry, boring, and repetitive. The two exams he gives are 25 multiple choice questions each with a long essay response as well. He also has you do a research paper that makes up a big portion of your grade.

She's amazing and very helpful. Class material isn't hard and she makes it very interesting as well. My advice is to read/skim the book and know everything in your notes to be prepared for the quizzes. Do your research credits as soon as possible because it's very easy and do an extra one to boost your grade. Attendance is very important for notes.

Dr.  is an exceptional at what she does. She genuinely cares about her students and their successes. Go to office hours, and she will give you clear guidance to pass the class. There are a few chances for extra credit which will boost your grade along with SONA credit. I am glad I took her class and would take her again in a heartbeat.

Dr. J is THE BEST professor. She's such a genuine person and you can tell she cares about her students, as well as Psych. Be ready to take tons of notes though. She tries her best to make the class seem as interesting as possible by bringing props and allowing discussion. She does a lot if in-class review and tests are super easy.

Loved ! She made everything so clear and easy. If you attend class, you'll understand. We used clickers, she shows movies and provides great examples and activities so the class was very hands on in a way.

Condescending.Always acts like she is 'out to get you'. She is smart, I'll give you that. But its gone to her head a bit. Being smart doesn't matter if you can't communicate effectively with your students.
good luck w this one
She is definitely a bully. I have never had an instructor who treated students as terribly as she does. Individuals quit the program specifically because of her.

If she decides she doesn't like you, watch out; it will be her mission to make your life miserable. If she really does not like you, her criticism and discrimination will continue after you have completed her course because she will make sure to tell everyone in the department how terrible she thinks you are. She is a bully.

Don't take the class, i thought i could get through it but i was wrong. It is so so boring, i actually fell asleep during lecture in a huge lecture hall. Material is difficult which i do not understand since it is just an intro class. she also assigns busy work that is completely pointless. And she is annoying-exaggerates her lame east coast accent
This lady is terrible. Bad at lecturing, bad at helping, bad overall.

Class is harder than it needs to be but get to drop 1 exam grade. She was nice to me when I talked to her. I agree the tests are tricky and throw in random facts from the book that weren't on the study guide.
Fantastic lectures filled with debates over cases and decisions surrounding law. He is a great guy. Would recommend if you are at all interested in law and or an easy A.

is an awesome prof. Many of the classes were just class discussions based on topics like affirmative action, juries, eyewitness testimonies, etc. Very funny and, if you actually show up to lecture, the tests are extremely straight forward. Posts slides on Carmen, but they don't have much info so you have to go to lecture, but he makes them fun

She is a pretty laid back prof. Everything you need for the exams are in the notes you should be taking. She does give home, but it is pretty easy. She is a tough grader when it comes to it, but it's just common sense. She can be stern when she needs to, but if you follow her rules, which are pretty insignificant, you'll do great.
She's very fair. I got away with calling Karl Marx and idiot and still got an A or A-. Don't be a child and you will be fine.

Definitely not "the greatest thing since slice bread", if you know what I mean. If you miss one day in that class, you are setting yourself up for failure, especially when she doesn't do any make-up assignments. Her grading style is difficult to understand and unfair. Good luck if you take this class, you're going to need it.
She's not personal, almost to a harsh point. The class as a whole was interesting but the way she goes about teaching it is awful, the textbook is clearer than she ever was.

is an unpopular Sociology professor at OSU Marion. She has a cold personality. I received As & Bs on almost every test and paper, but missed a few classes because I was sick. She was puzzled on why I was doing well in her class, but somehow I ended up with a C as a final grade. I have received As in all my other Soc classes.

Dean  is a good teacher. He is very informative and does a great job relating the topics to more recent elections. The class can get boring at times, but it is very interesting. The class is not too difficult and the paper topic is very interesting.
Very nice man, interesting class; genuinely decent human being and very bright man.
Easy but boring.

This class is not as bad as it may seem. He is a practicing psychologist so he lectures on what he thinks is interesting and then you are responsible for what is in the book for the exam. He loves statistics so pay close attention to them while your taking book notes. He also gives a pretty big curve which helps a lot. I got an A fairly easily.

The tests in this class were ridiculous, they are made up of totally random questions from the book. I found the lecture parts of the test to be quite easy, but his lectures are boring and the research is outdated. There is no new info to be learned in this class if you have already taken counseling psych and abnormal psych.

Dr.  was extremely spacey, disorganized and dull. His lectures sometimes have information that is incorrect and misleading. He relies HEAVILY on insignificant details from the book. If you read the book then that part of the test is fine, but the lecture section is ridiculous. The paper, however, was easy.

He makes mistakes on his own exams, makes you choose between what he says in class and what the book says, and if that's not enough, you spend half the time trying to figure out what the questions are asking. Nice guy, but extremely spacey, making for an unreliable professor.

The class is not hard if you life cold hard stats. Half of exam comes from the book (which you never go over and is indep study) and lectures that are based on date he has found on diff. subjects. He comes off anxious and is pretty scatter-brained, unprepared. His off the cuff style does not work. 3 exams and a an easy paper. Take only if needed.
This professor constantly generalizes about disorders, uses outdated research, and is super terrible at writing exams. good luck, i would not recommend him, he needs to retire

This man has no buisiness being a college proffesor.
  If a student asks a question which he doesn't know the answer to, he just guesses, often times wrongly.
  The subject matter is very easy to master, yet it is nearly impossible to get an A. This is because his tests include many random and irrelavent statistics from the text book.

Dr.  is an excellent professor. He really cares about his student's success. His course is very well-organized and he does as much as he can to make a course of this difficulty accessible to his students. The only note was some of the readings were really long, over 100 pages, and could have easily been assigned with only the abstract.

Very, very boring lectures. Stays on the same slide for an hour. Attendance does matter because you do writing assignments in each class. Very boring and drawn out talks but easy class. Tests aren't too bad as long as you study.

Overall a pretty easy class if you do the readings and attend class to complete critical thinking written assignments (1-2 paragraphs). Lectures are extremely boring. I think this class could be really interesting if taught by a different professor. If you want to attend jailprison tours, don't schedule class after this one.

Overall solid professor. Class can seem a bit slow at times and he isn't the best with powerpoint, but he certainly knows his stuff. If you attend class, pay attention, and do the in class writings, it's hard to get a bad grade. Exams are easy, and he look like Tobias from Arrested Development without a mustache. Solid dude
Boring. Bad use of powerpoint.

I actually enjoyed this class with Professor . His exams are pretty easy as long as you read the chapters and attend class. Complete the critical thinking questions and it is hard to get a bad grade in this class. He knows what he's talking about and invites you on jail visits with his higher level classes! I'd take a class with him again
Extremely boring teacher, speaks mono-tone the whole time. Makes harder to understand than it should be.

The previous two post say it well. He stands in front of the class and simply lectures from the book, he's more than boring, and he makes the class harder than it needs to be. He does provide his slides but not until a couple days before the test. He gives absolutely NO review and you're on your own for the tests. Very disappointed in this teacher.

3 MC tests. Seemed to stretch for material on a few of the questions. Lectures were pretty boring. Had 1-3 opinion questions that you had to hand in at the end of each class. Just hand in something and you are good. These were worth a solid % of the grade and worth the effort.

Dr.  is a very nice professor and really wants students to do well-- she even brought snacks to lecture for students multiple times! Her exams are almost exactly the same questions as her quizzes, so make sure to review those often. There is a weekly online quiz but otherwise exams are just quizzes and exact lecture slides. Not a bad class!
is an extremely boring lecturer, however her exams are made up of exactly what is posted on the slides, so memorize these! You do not need to attend lecture to get a good grade in this class.

She obviously knows what she is talking about in regards to the class. However, students did not know that much, and she was not super clear in what was expected. Multiple times I got points taken off for things I would have done if I would have been told to do so. Also, attendance "wasn't mandatory", but she did random attendance checks.

Dr.  is one of the best professors I have had at OSU. Funny, engaging, and eccentric. Cheat sheets for exams, but make sure you go to class and pay moderate attention because the slides are not self-explanatory.

He's an eccentric and funny guy with excellent music taste. Initially, I was intimidated and scared for my wellbeing in this class, but because he's very good at explaining and teaching, I ended up doing very well. He also gives good feedback if you meet with him during office hours.

A very funny professor who always asks us to "bombard" him with questions and is very quick to respond to emails. He provides full and short lectures on each chapter and puts an emphasis on individual exploration. We had a weekly quiz, discussion posts, questions, journal entry/ activity, and a quiz make-up activity with no exams or tests.

She's clear as mud when it comes to everything--almost as if she is writing her dissertation on academic vagueness. Lectures are not mandatory but she throws in all sorts of attendance checks and participation activities, so you better attend. I was excited for the group project but I was stuck doing all of the work and it really dragged on.

Dr.  is funny & relatable, but I did not like his course, he's unprofessional and swears a lot, and although the tests are relatively easy, the format rubbed me the wrong way. Plus, when I took his class, I missed a thing or a religious holiday, and he wouldn't let me make it up. That assignment was the difference between an A- and B+ for me.

Very unreasonable and harsh with grading group work. She would basically laugh us off when we went to her for help/clarification. She's absolutely brilliant and dedicated to her studies but I don't think she understood that her students aren't at the same level of knowledge as she is. She's moving to DC so luckily you probably won't have her.
A very good professor - I really enjoyed attending his lectures. He's extremely knowledgeable on this subject and is genuinely interested in teaching. Awesome prof, awesome class!

Terrible terrible terrible terrible professor!!!! I can't even explain how much I hated his class. I am very interested in this topic and he made me hate it. Sitting through his classes is the worst experience ever. He speaks incredibly slowly and in a monotone voice and does absolutely nothing for his students. Never goes over tests. AVOID!!!!!!!!

There was a lot of talk about neurotransmitters and whatnot, which I wasn't prepared for and his monotone voice made lectures kind of painful to sit through; however,if you study the powerpoints he posts on carmen, you will do well in the class. Also, if you do well on the first two exams, you are done for the quarter!

Definitely a lot harder then it seems. A lot of memorizing technical drug names and history of drug use. Tricky test questions and a TON of material to learn. Does not give +/- only A,B,C,D. Test averages in my class were low 70%. It's also really hard to listen to his voice during class and he goes really quick through the slides. AVOID!!

This class should be named Into to Neuropharmacology. Avoid if you are dumb about Psychiatry and drugs. You'll be memorizing pill names and what receptors they hit. I got a B by looking at the powerpoints the night before. that's only because of my previous intrest in crazy meds. Tough class for most, although heavily curved.
This class should be taught online. There is no reason to go to class. All he does is read directly from the slides. His exams are hard... but his curve in the end is nice. Lectures are VERY boring!

Interesting material. DO NOT BUY BOOK!! You will never open it. His powerpoints come straight from book and test question come straight from powerpoints. Class becomes a bit boring after awhile. Best 2 out of 3 on your test grades. Failry hard class. I still recommend it.

He LITERALLY reads right from the powerpoint slides, so if it's in outline form, don't expect him to make clear sentences and explain further then what is stated on the slide. slides posted online, study from those. grade is based off 2 out of 3 tests. You drop your lowest test. easy if you study the slides that he tells you to for the tests.

Another class where the only grades are a 50% midterm and a 50% final. I hate that. I don't think there was any curve so if you moderately screw one up, well, you are kinda just screwed in general. He seems like a nice guy but after a week you will probably get bored of his lectures and just stop going. Just download/study from the powerpoints.

He wasn't the most well organized prof, but lectures are interesting and he fosters discussion very well. Tests were difficult, if you didn't study. He is very willing to help, but you have to ask for it first! Just because you didn't study and didn't get an A doesn't make it a bad class or him a bad prof.
So disappointed. He is so unclear and the tests are hard!
Has no clue what she's doing. She spends more time correcting her mistakes and rushing through material than actually explaining the material. A straight Stats class would be more helpful.
Terrible. Her lectures and notes drag on forever. The TA was awful as his e-mails and exams were riddled with poor grammar and contradictions. This class was a complete waste of time.
Dr.  is awesome. She's funny and adorably awkward if I weren't graduating I'd try to take more classes from her. Doesn't make you buy a book either!

take your next class with prof !! she's awesome...always ends class 15 mins early, puts all notes up on power point. only 3 homework assignments and 3 exams. the homework was quite easy, and the exams are all 50 mc questions. her wording can be a bit misleading, but if you get less than a B you're an idiot

As long as you read the text or go to lecture, the tests are cake. I went to lecture more than half the time, but it wasn't really necessary. He was pretty funny and the lectures were not bad at all. Do the 3 hw assignments just in case you bomb a test. He doesnt curve your grade, so you get what you get. Great professor though.

This class was bad, I had to drop it! The information is sooo boring and Dr.  was a very stiff teacher. I felt like he wasn't approachable at all. He told us to refer all questions to the TA! Tests are soo hard. Only good thing about the class was the optional surveys or paper for 50 points extra credit. Dont take unless life depends on it.

Dr.  is a hard teacher. I would not recommend him. When he asks questions in class and students answer the question wrong he puts them down and makes them feel dumb. He does offer extra credit though, and the homeworks are not that hard. Watch out for the tests they can be killers.

Dr.  is a very difficult professor to work with and does not respect her students. When difficult situations arise in the classroom she's been shown to handle them extremely unfairly and without respect and careful consideration. If you're looking for fair treatment and respect from your professor I would not recommend Dr. .
He is kind of arrogant and extremely boring- class not recommended.
Great teacher! Tests are all essay, but he grades them very fairly. But bring a pillow on presentaion days, that's a bore!

Professor  is a decent professor at OSU Mansfield. She remains unbiased in the politics class, even though her opinion on the matter is clear. She is easy to get along with, and is quite understanding when you must miss a class. However, some of her material is difficult to understand. I often found myself using Google to look up answers.

I loved her class! She gives great feedback and goes above and beyond for her students. I loved how she makes sure everyone is involved in class discussions, but does not call on people if they do not know the answer. She also lets you use a cheat sheet on the midterm, and you get a take-home final. Be sure to pay attention and take good notes.

Heavy weighted classes. Would not recommend anyone to take her classes. They're boring as is her teaching style and personality. I took two of her classes. She's only there for her research funding. Snobby too, with no reason to be.

Had for Poly Sci 101 & 512. Unprofessional. Class time was half spent discussing readings that had nothing to do with the lecture which followed. Did not use Carmen. Found these classes unchallenging and came out with the same knowledge I had going in. Text books were not wisely chosen.

I liked taking his class but I have to say it's quite repetitive. Yeah you learn a lot but it's super boring sometimes. You can easily pass the class with an A by just using sparknotes and not reading the 2 hours of homework he wants you to do by the next lecture. But he is very knowledgeable and friendly I liked him overall just kinda boring.

I took this class as an online Diversity GE, and it was very interesting! workload is quite manageable each week as well. One thing I will say that exams make up a large portion of your grade, but those are hardly challenging. Other than that, just weekly discussion posts and 1 paper. Great choice for a GE.

Such an easy A and she is honestly the best! Her lectures are so interesting and there is an extra credit assignment worth 3%. The 2 papers are relatively easy and she is very willing to help and give feedback if you need it. Definitely recommend!!

She gives a lot of work and the class requires you to read the entire textbook due to inquizitive. She does seem like she cares about the students but thats hard to display in an online course. There are no cumulative exams, just quizzes every other week on the chapters we worked on. There also is no final.
Exceptional professor and made one of my first classes at OSU enjoyable!

Professor  is awesome! I learned so much from this class and would definitely take her again. Assignments and tests are straightforward, and there are extra credit opportunities. If you just pay attention during lecture and have a rough understanding of the weekly articles, you'll be fine. Overall this was a very easy class.

A good course to fill your schedule with if you're already slammed. The assignments are very short and she gives guided notes for you to write in while reading the textbook. If you pay attention to the material and put effort into discussions/journals, you're sure to get an A

Do not take 3780! They "teach" you with YouTube videos that are all four years out of date! Recitation is basically just graduate students trying to help you with all the problems you'll inevitably encounter, again, because they don't teach you! The videos weren't even made for this course, they're recycled from another! BEYOND LAZY!

Class was interesting; prof has a great sense of humor (and the best name ever). Midterm and final aren't as impossible as everyone's saying; I didn't do any of the readings (didn't even buy the books) and I got a B+ in the class. Just pay attention in recitation and you should pick up the book material.

There are an insane amount of readings assigned, and they're the key to passing the multiple choice section of exams. He comes off as slightly pretentious, but he makes lecture fun to listen to. It's a lot of material, but a decent curve, mixed with a paper that takes a large chunk of the grade as well as mandatory recitation.

One of the best professors I've ever had. Lecture is terse, but very well-structured and you'll learn more in half an hour with him than many professors can in a quarter. Exams are challenging, so study well. Lectures are very fun as well, and usually include video or audio clips to keep things interesting.

Lectures are actually really interesting and well put together, but he is pretty arrogant (though funny sometimes). Tests are VERY hard and totally unrealistic. TA said there were a lot of grad school questions on midterm. HAVE to do reading to know what the tests are talking about. I wouldn't take him again, just because tests are impossible.

is the funniest professor I have ever had, and every lecture was interesting and got everyone thinking and involved. I highly recommend  and this course. He literally had the whole room cracking up. Driest sense of humor ever. Plus, I cannot stress how insanely cool the name "" is.
was pretty arrogant. His lectures could be fairly entertaining but he was constantly unclear as to what was required.

she was horrible! during office hours she made her students feel stupid for asking questions. isn't that what office hours are for? she thinks she's better than everyone and gives you a bad grade if you can't read her mind. DO NOT take class with her. i always get A's in psych... it's my major.I got a C in her class!

One of the worst professors I have ever had. I do not doubt she is intelligent however her job is to teach... and at this I give her an F. She seems arrogant and god forbid you miss a class... she is not helpful. I found her rather rude.DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS WITH HER.
Really knows his stuff and interested in teaching. Don't take his class early in the day though, his voice will put you to sleep fast.

Never know what is going to be on exams - there have been times I've tried to look up questions after the test and either couldn't find them at all in the lecture notes or text, or they came from chapters not even covered yet.. Also a rather rude/superior attitude..

Took this class as a GE and honestly, worst decision of my life. Professor is absolute, GARBAGE. She said all semester, I will give opportunities to participate in research for extra credit, AND SHE NEVER DID. She also clearly stated in the syllabus, and in emails too, that she would give ONE MINUTE PER QUESTION ON QUIZZES, which NEVER happened.

Dr.  is amazingly accomplished and a great lecturer. She really knows her material; her powerpoints and lectures make the material very clear especially for tests and papers. The class is easy if you go and pay attention.
She is one my my least favorite teachers I have probably had. Her attitude is always negative and is not helpful at all.
Professor  is extremely intelligent and very knowledgable about her field. If you attend lecture and do the required readings this class is a cakewalk. It doesn't hurt that she's good looking.

Totally don't recommend her for a professor. For goodness sake, it is an introduction to psychology class and it's extremely intense for no reason. Her lectures make no sense and she doesn't give good criteria as to what the test would be like. Avoid her if you can....

Dr.  is a great lecturer. His exams can be tough but you at least feel like you are learning something in that class instead of just regurgitating information like you have to do for most classes. If you actually want to learn neuroscience then take this class.

This guy is in need of an honest review. No doubt, he is a great lecturer but he is never available. I'm pretty sure his office hours don't meet the university's minimum requirements. The class structure is inherently flawed as it is only out of 80 points. His mult. choice questions aren't hard, they're merely convoluted. Most over rated professor.

He doesn't take attendance, but it is impossible to do well without attending lecture. If you attend lecture, pay attention, take good notes, and study hard you can do well. This isn't an easy class and not really psychology. It's studying the advanced physiology and neuroscience of the human brain and neurological disorders. Loved it and the prof
interesting - but monotonic...
Excellent teacher, brilliant person. he expects a lot but he is very helpful to anyone who really wants to learn

Try to avoid this professor at all costs. Lectures everyday, at least 50 pages of reading per night from the textbook. VERY difficult grader. Be prepared to be yelled at A LOT. She gets very upset when students do not understand the subjects at the level she does. If you haven't already look her up! She doesn't care about her students whatsoever.

As long as you do the readings from the textbook you will receive an 'A'. My only complaint is that she will go off on liberal tangents and went as far as to say, "Why don't white people just shut up!" as if to say white people didn't have grounds to talk about minority issues.

Her class wasn't hard, and she had notes on Carmen which helped a lot since you couldn't really keep up with the slides and her talking. No final just a really easy paper. And the quizzes and test weren't hard at all.

I took this class with  Harvey during my freshman year at Ohio State. Even now as a senior, it still stands out in my head as the worst experience I've had at OSU and is also by far the worst grade I have ever received in college. She's an unfair grader and a poor lecturer. Look at her Arizona State listing for more information.
I enjoyed the class alot. The professor was very interested in the subject, but made it difficult to participate in class discussions. But she is very understanding and a lenient grader.

i loved this class,  worked so hard to pull it together. she put a lot of pressure on us, and sometimes it was really frustrating, like she needed a chill pill, but well worth it, and i totally respect her for it.

She is very nice and very smart. She expects things to be in when she says they need to be in. I learned a lot from her but it wasn't really exciting. She talks a lot and shows power points. The movies she shows are great, and the material isn't to hard. The exams are long I suggest studying!!

If you can avoid professor , DO IT. A ridiculous amount of work for no reason. Extremely harsh grader. I was literally.5% away from an A and she refused to offer anything. Which isn't the end of the world, but overall her class just feels like a bunch of busy work and like she takes off points just cause she feels like it.
Class is clear and easy to follow. Variety of material so it doesn't get boring. Quizzes aren't too difficult. Opportunities for extra credit. Would reccomend.

Dr.  was a very good professor. I really had no interest in judgement and decision making before I entered his classroom but now I have a new understanding and respect for the subject matter. The only complaints that I would have would be we did not have a textbook which made things hard. The class is clenging but very interesting.

She is a good teacher. Likes to talk a lot and gets everyone involved. She is a tough grader on her exams but easy with the papers. You have to do a ton of work in this class and must show interest or she won't give you the grade you deserve. She is fair, but if you don't like to read and write, avoid her class. Lots of discussions (10%) of grade.

I did not care for Professor  one bit. She didnt really seem to know what she was talking about. She was quite ditzy at times and laughed at the mistakes that she made often.She assigns too much reading for the amount of assignments she expects you to do.
She is a very nice professor and gives out lots of extra credit. Sometimes a fast talker but overall helpful.
Takes TopHat attendance (ends up being 15% of grade); uploads lectures online, but in a very confusing manner; exams are impossible as he asks for minute details briefly mentioned in slides.

If you aren't considering law school, or you don't have an interest in the Supreme Court, DO NOT TAKE THIS COURSE. That said,  is brilliant and highly regarded, look at his CV. He's extremely kind and helpful in office hours. Lectures are rough, he will lecture AT you for 80 minutes without stopping. Read every case and BRIEF THEM.

Material is interesting, but there's a lot of it. Professor  makes pretty confusing Powerpoint slides that don't help much, and will sometimes breeze through confusing concepts without clarifying or connecting them to broader ideas. Read the text before lecture to get the most out of his class.

Professor 's lectures might be the cure to narcolepsy. He definitely knows his material but has no idea how to convey it. His notes are filled with acronyms that you will have no idea what they stand for when you go to prepare for his exams. He also uses terms that he does not go over and assumes you know what he's talking about.

Worst polisci class I have taken at OSU. Like every1 says on here, multiple choice exams in which 1 word makes the difference if you get the ? right. Lectures, textbook, and online notes, are not helpful. attendance is a part of your grade (you will be board). If it was not for the curve, many students would end up with D's and F's. AVOID HIM!!!!!!

Worst class I have ever taken. Clearly knows his stuff,but can't communicate that with the average student. He's also a law school prof and teaches the class like we're all about to pass the bar tomorrow. To pass an exam is to have an angel on your side. Do yourself a favor and pick a different class, or drop while you still have time.

As an aspiring law student, his tests are multiple choice and extremely unpractical. Exams are on Carmen, which tends to glitch and mess up your answers. It gives you no room to make your case like an actual law exam. He uses this STUPID attendance taking software called Tophat that you'll waste $20 on. Don't waste time. Find a better class.

Terrible professor in a sense that he is VERY BORING. Exams are open booknotes, but WATCH OUT ! He'll put a lot of questions with: A,B,C,D, All of the above, none of the above, BC, AD? the answers will sometimes come down to a single word that makes the difference. Unless you plan on going to law school, there is no benefit in taking this course.
Useful class but so boring you'll want to die. Tests are HARD despite being open book. Prof's notes are posted online but are extremely disorganized. Final exam looked nothing like the midterm.

kinda boring, we just reviewed court briefs and that's it. there are three grades: exam one, final exam, and attendance. exams are open book and open note, but don't let that fool you; they are incredibly hard and often the difference between two potential answers for a question is a single word. there is a curve, but you may need all of it.
AVOID AT ALL COSTS. This guy is HORRIBLE. No interest in teaching whatsoever, exams are horrible...AVOID.

Extremely nice professor and very helpful...bring a pillow to class because his lectures are very boring. Seems very interested in the topics covered but he's the opposite when it comes to teaching...open book/note tests
Had him for psych 1100; a great choice for my first college class. Thought it was pretty easy. He curved most our tests 6-10 points. Was very happy with the overall experience.

Lectures are long and boring. He claims his test material comes out of the slides, but I found the book way more helpful. Tests are very difficult, but he curves them, which helps a lot. Difficult, but technically do-able class. On an unrelated note: he's kinda hot in a bizarre way

Super friendly and helpful. Lectures could get dry, but the material is really interesting. He tries to stick to what you need to know, but will also go more in depth if people ask. You can really see his passion for the field even though he is a bit monotone.

Super nice guy, crazy-making quiet/scattered lecturer. If you don't know much about neuroscience you'll have to teach yourself from the book (what I did) or spend lots of time with him one-on-one. He's probably much better for advanced students.

This professor is very boring. It is very tempting to just skip class and teach yourself from the book. He is helpful one on one because you can constantly ask questions. For such a boring class, it didn't help that he didn't provide any way of making it interesting. This class is required for my major and I might have to retake it, yikes!

She is AMAZING! She gives interesting lectures(cute memes) and offers study guides before exams. If you do them, you will do well in the exams. Papers are graded clearly and have rubrics(useful) beforehand. Attendance is not required unless there is an activity on that day. The activities are funny and not difficult. Assignments are easy.

The most boring class of my existence. Make sure you peep her extra credit point, as it would've allowed for me to not take the final haha. Basically you can schedule this class and only show up for exams and be 100% fine. It just is a drag. She will throw shade at you if you are not paying attention in lecture. This includes being on your laptop.

Awesome professor! Interesting class, AND a very easy A!Despite the easy tests, you learned a lot in this class. Study the study guide and you'll enjoy the class without stressing yourself out. You also get to drop a midterm/the final if you did well enough on the other exams. More teachers should be like this!
Definitely a good professor and loves what she does. Very straightforward with what you need to know which helps a lot to do well overall. I would recommend her!

I strongly recommend not taking a course with this professor. I'm currently writing this review while sitting in his class, which I just dropped after two days because I decided I can't spend the entire semester with this instructor. He is very rude and condescending in his delivery of the material. Do yourself a favor and take a different class.

Many questions are completely ambiguous or have conflicting information which makes the midterm luck-based. Everyone ran out of time, average was initially an 80%. Now it's a 78%, and we're confused whether he curved it down? No lecture recs, mandatory attendance, midterms open at 9AM for 1 hour, & no slides released until weeks after his lectures.

Great guy. Loved 4136 with him, so I took this class. Anyone with any interest in the Supreme Court should take him; you will learn so much. This class wasn't as good; I'd already learned about a lot of material in his other course. Still valuable research and writing skills. He provides copious guidelines for the paper. Do that and you'll be ok.
Tough class and confusion around some expectations but with effort I did learn a lot.

The worst instructor I've ever had. Constantly left class wondering why this is the education I'm paying for. Constantly wasted class time. Never responded to emails. Unclear about every aspect of class (material, schedule, plan, grading, questions). Got mad/aggressive when we didn't understand things but expected us to respond perfectly.

Terrible professor that obviously does not care about his students. Seems like his entire class is created in one night. Everything is disjointed and never gives clear grading criteria (0 rubrics or guidelines), but expects students to respond perfectly to his assignments. Slow grader, terrible communication, seems confused about his own courses.

The worst professor I have had in my 4 yrs of college. Will not give direct responses to questions, very unorganized PowerPoints, very unorganized plan for syllabus and assignments, gets angry at students when they don't respond the way he wants. Does NOT properly explain anything. leaves students feeling very confused. Do not take his classes

He is the worst professor I have ever had. He literally doesn't answer your questions he just leads you on with more unanswered questions. He sucks at lecturing, he goes super fast and expects people to participate but yet makes you feel dumb when you don't give him the response he wants.

is probably the worst professor I've ever had. Clearly has absolutely no idea what he is doing and sits in class and reads out of the textbook. Doesn't answer emails even after being called out. Gets overly mad when students don't read the textbook, but he sits in lecture and directly reads out of it.
DO NOT TAKE HIS CLASS!!!!!!

This is one of the most interesting classes I have ever taken. While the class is very difficult (beware if you just want a grade booster), he is really passionate about the subject and I learned a lot more about the Supreme Court. The papers are long and difficult to write (20 page final paper), but it will turn out alright if you put in the work!

Showing up for class isn't mandatory, but its a good idea; he goes over a lot of stuff in class and makes things a lot easier to understand. Exams are important, so STUDY, but he's pretty generous about curves.
Very good. Dont miss class because a lot of material will be covered in one class time. must take good notes. Overall not a bad class, great prof.
Awesome if challenging professor!
Thinks he's above students, boring, lets his TA do the work, the paper and exams were tough and harshly graded. I go out of my way to not take his classes. On the positive side he knows his stuff.

His energy of strong interest in the subject matter is highly contagious. Relates themes well to real world change. Taking notes is a strong requirement for success on the quizzes and exams, the latter having above average difficulty. Solid Five Star Recommend.

By far one of my favorite professors at OSU. His class had challenging material, but none of the assignments or exams are extremely difficult and he is great about implementing feedback. He also gave an easy extra credit assignment. I wish I had taken more classes with him while at OSU.

He's passionate and lecture isn't bad, but he goes off on tangents sometimes. Slides are poor and bare minimum. Midterm and final were cake, but the quizzes are a bit difficult and worth 100 points! A paper of five pages is only worth 10 points, though....?

Hard class (especially for an intro, 200-level class), I don't recommend it unless you're looking for a challenge. Prof is very smart but dry, and digresses a lot. Text readings are long and became unnecessary. 3 pop quizzes, a 5 page paper, midterm (mostly essay), & final (mostly essay). Honestly I'm just reallllly happy that this class is over.
Interesting and easy class. Professor is a great guy!

My favorite class I've ever taken was the one I took with him. He doesn't take attendance (though he notices those who show up) but GO TO CLASS. He's a great lecturer and if you know your lectures and cases you'll be fine . Sit towards the front to be one of Larry's favorites. You'll just want him to like you. It'll just make you feel good.

Dr.  is willing to help students. There are a lot of readings which take a huge amount of time but that is definitely necessary to learn psychology. A quiz every single class but it ensures that you would read. Exams are not hard, and there are extra credits.

This was his first semester teaching this class so it was kinda disorganized, but still very easy A. He had all the exams take home, open note, online so that was nice. Honestly learned more from the book than class, but he does easy reading quizzes every class so you have to show up.

AU14: Lectures can be helpful but if you read the textbook it is basically the same thing. I read the text for every chapter which was time consuming but made everything easier. Lectures not mandatory, hes a nice guy, grades things easily, tests are department tests, no quizzes or homework. Tests are hard so you better make time to read.

Dr.  is a nice guy. Really dedicated to his students and their learning. Lays class out clearly, easy to contact. Tests are very straightforward. Study your online lecture notes and you can do well. There are flashcards on studyblue which are pretty helpful if you don't have time to make them. Study hard, stay on top of things and it's easy.

his lectures were very repetitive and made little sense, i dont recommend if you need to actually learn the coursework, but he is okay if you just need a GE credit, three midterms and 3/4 quizzes and the final are the only things graded. the class is based off of 100 points and every point is 1% of your final grade, very weird guy overall

Professor  was great! His lectures were very interesting. He only graded based off of tests and quizzes, so you have to do well on those to pass the class. As long as you pay attention in lectures, especially review lectures, you should do well.

Professor  is very nice and I found the class decently interesting just very repetitive. The review lectures prep you for quizzes and tests very well. Very organized in the online format and very little work to do. Just 5 quizzes and 2 tests are graded.

Prof. 's class is just all about lectures. He's a very chill man, maybe a little too chill. If you have no interest in Epidemiology, you will likely find this class super boring. Review his PowerPoints and you will do fine on your exams. Epidemiology isn't of my interest, so it's not really for me. He's a helpful man though.

You don't need to attend lectures or read the book. I am an epidemiology minor and even I found his lectures to be boring. Attend the review session and read over the review slides and you'll do well. He is very kind, but boring.

Extremely boring lectures. He just reads from the slides so attendance isn't mandatory. The slides are very hard to look at. Not sure why, but he chooses to make his slides yellow text on a bright blue background. Sounds like a Michigan fan-probably added to why I didn't like him. There are no homeworks or quizzes, just the midterm and final.

This class consists of the option between weekly discussion posts or a 15 page paper due at the end of the semester, weekly quizzes, and a few exams.  lectures about random things instead of the actual graded material during lectures, while also pushing questionable political narratives within the course material.

Specifically for branch campus students, he is the absolute worst. He doesnt care about the other campuses at all. Your grade depends one one group project that hell give little feedback for. Its required though, so best of luck

If you are interested in going through 5 minutes of slides during class & then discussing current events or his/other students personal & often unrelated experiences, take Curts class. Professor  is a really great professor. He is clear about what his expectations are for your assignments. There are 2 midterms, 1 final. Lots of extra credit opportunity and he also curves almost all the exams. He is very smart and yet is easy to learn from as he explains things flawlessly. He is also funny and really nice!

COVID-19: His response to courses going virtual was amazing. All lectures were asynchronous, except group project meetings every few weeks. Instead of lectures, he made overview videos that summarized important points. Did a mid-class survey to check in with students and was willing to make changes. Plenty of opportunities for points via quizzes.

The WORST psych professor I have ever had. The textbook is $200 & he refuses to post the slides. Gives you a week's worth of information every single class. Has the most unclear grading criteria & gives you a bad grade for not knowing what he wanted. Gave ONE paragraph of instructions on the huge semester long project. Avoid him if you can!

She is honestly the most caring person ever. Dont skip class and you will 100% get an A. The exams are pretty easy if you just read the textbook chapters before the test, but she structures the class so that even if you dont test well but come to class you will get an A. All the other assignments are crazy easy.

I took Juvenile Delinquency with her and it was awesome! She loves what she teaches and that comes across clearly in her lectures. There are a lot of little assignments on Carmen but they're straightforward and easy. The exams are easy after a quick review of the book chapters. Definitely take this class with her!!

good lecturer, but I have find him biased individual.sometimes his tone comes out to resemble State Department spokesperson. otherwise great selection of the Academic journals(mostly current). I would encourage anyone who has serious interest of IR or U.S foreign policy to take this class with him.

A mess of a prof, no direction in lecture, impossible to take notes and study for exams. The only fun/useful part of the whole class is the strategy game you play the second half. But its in a building that is RIDICULOUSLY far away and there is no indication of this when you sign up.

Absolutely loved this class and this man! It was so interesting and he's incredibly smart. You should really go to class and if you get into the assignments, you can come out of the class with vast knowledge on the subject matter. I would even take it again someday (and might audit it..). Definitely take it if you like international relations!

Very challenging professor... the class is graded strictly on how everyone else in the class performs in the class... the exams are very difficult because you need to write exactly what he wants you to know- just do the readings and reread everything before the exams and go to all of the study groups and you'll be fine

I think the Department's high placement in the national rankings has a lot to do with Dr. . I'm in graduate school now, and his courses were bar-none the best preparation I received as an undergrad. He's the real thing-- don't waste his time.

Dr.  is a great professor and professional. He is very supportive of his students while keeping an engaging course. He continues to support his students even after they have moved on from his course in professional matters.

Dr. T was a great professor and taught me a lot. Lectures were only once a week, but they were great and I learned a lot. There were discussion posts every week, 3 exams, and a paper. I really liked this class and I really recommend.

Worst teacher I've ever had. He didn't put any effort at all into the class but expected us to go above and beyond. The material wasn't relevant to our program, and the test wasn't relevant to the material.
In love with his accent.

He does not use any kind of slides or another presentation tool in class, he talks at you for 1:20 straight. This class was also graded solely on exams, which is not something I enjoy. I found recording the lectures to be somewhat helpful, but overall was not a fan of him at all. He is also confusing, sometimes going back on what he said before.

Dr.  was a nice British guy. His midterms are fairly easy, although it's difficult to get a perfect due to the fill in the blank section. Fun class, easy to understand, and if you go to lecture, easy A. Tests are lecture based.

I love his class. He's funny and very enthusiastic about the subject matter, which makes it much more interesting. Grade is based entirely on 2 tests, but his grading is flexible. Also, he has a fun English accent. Overall, great professor! Take his class!

Awesome guy, extremely nice, but I did not like the class. Discussions are interesting enough, the project is easy, but the exams suck. They cover an enormous amount of information and it's difficult to know exactly what to study.
I'm a 100% hetero guy, and this man is adorable. He is so animated and his accent just makes you pay attention to everything he says, pretty much my favorite class to go to ever.
Very great professor
Absolutely loved Dr. ! She is a fair grader with great feedback. You will need the book (you will use it for online quizzes & HW). I definitely recommend this class!
She was amazing!There were a lot of notes, but her lectures were fun. Also, make sure you pay attention to grammar in your papers. Loved her and her class.

I love , she's helpful and understanding and unlike some teachers you'll get she really cares about her students learning the material. Had a blast in the class and I am totally going to take her again.
Great Professor!!!

This is a brain dump class. There are so many notes and so many chapters covered per test (10 chapters) that it is hard to decide what is important. Memorize, memorize, memorize.. pass the test and then forget it. Anal retentive for sure, but organized and fair... just no life experience to go on.

Prof. 's course is largely statistical and focuses on the kinda stuff most political science students probably already know (at least in a loose sense). As such, lectures are quite boring and most of the information can be gathered from skimming the slides he provides. He's terribly dry but very smart, so you can't really help but respect him.

I really don't understand the hate for . This obviously isn't the most fun class, but it isn't hard either. Attendance is mandatory, but you pay to go to school here so just show up. Do not take public health data analytics. It was unclear and unorganized, though it was made sure that attendance was taken every class. Those who do not meet those criteria will struggle immensely, and you will not get help when you ask questions.

There are not enough characters to complain about how horrible this class was. Attendance every day, which forced you to sit through boring lectures when the slides are posted online anyways. Group projects are assigned by Dr. , and are groups of 10-11 people, which was impossible to coordinate. Grading is hard and instructions are vague.

Dr.  cares a lot about environmental health and it shows in lectures. Speaking of lectures, they are boring but you need to go for attendance. Quizzes are online and pretty easy but you better hope your group is responsive because mine sucked and I had to do a lot of the work for those four projects
Horrible, very unorganized, tough grader, he's friendly, but I really wouldn't recommend him.

Just Ridiculous, he makes his quizzes and tests based on things that aren't even discussed in the slides or lecture (???????). Everything about him and his class is so unorganized. I don't even know how or why OSU hired him. Just b/c someone has a Ph.D.. it doesn't mean they will be a good professor.

Wouldn't recommend taking this class with him. His lectures are boring and unclear. The papers are a large part of your grade, but are graded very arbitrarily. He's condescending and rude when spoken to in person. Makes it clear he doesn't want students to succeed. I learned nothing from this class and am avoiding any future classes taught by him.
This is his first semester teaching here. He is not as bad as the previous review. Need to take notes, slides are posted online but notes are needed to get decent grades on quizzes. No tests!
